2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
¾ cup Jasmine Rice
2 tbsp Soy Sauce
1 tbsp Sesame Oil
2 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
½ unit(s) Yellow Onion
56 g Edamame
1 unit(s) Carrot
9 g Sesame Seeds
2 tbsp Sweet Chili Sauce
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.12 tsp Pepper*

Add 1 cup (2 cups) water and 1/8 (1/4 tsp) tsp salt to a medium pot. Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Meanwhile, using a strainer, rinse rice until water runs clear.
Add rice and edamame to the boiling water, then reduce heat to medium-low. Cover and cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 12-14 min. (NOTE: Reduce heat to low if water is boiling over.)
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Meanwhile, peel, then mince or grate garlic.
Peel, then cut carrot into 1/4-inch half moons.
Peel, then cut onion into 1/4-inch slices.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
When hot, add sesame seeds to the dry pan. Toast, stirring often, until fragrant, 3-4 min. (TIP: Keep your eye on them so they don't burn!) Transfer to a plate.

Add half the sesame oil to the same pan (used in step 3), then onions and carrots. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 3-4 min.
Season with salt and pepper, then transfer to a plate. Cover to keep warm.

Add remaining sesame oil to the same pan, then Beyond Meat® and patties and garlic. Cook, breaking up patties into bite-sized pieces, until crispy, 5-6 mins.**
Add soy sauce and half the sweet chili sauce. Cook, stirring often, until Beyond Meat® is coated, 2-3 min.
Stir in half the sesame seeds.
Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff rice with a fork.
Divide rice between bowls.
Top with veggies, then Beyond Meat® mixture.
Drizzle remaining sweet chili sauce over top.
Sprinkle with remaining sesame seeds.